---
import { getPostBySlug } from "./posts";
const post = getPostBySlug("welcome-to-my-blog")!;
import "../../styles/blog.css";
---

<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<meta charset="UTF-8" />
		<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
		<title>{post.title} - XAAANE</title>
		<link rel="icon" type="image/png" href="/flavicon.png" />
		<style>
			/* Unique styles for this post */
			body {
				line-height: 1.6;
			}

			.post-header {
				margin-bottom: 3rem;
			}

			h1 {
				font-size: 2.5rem;
			}

			.post-content {
				line-height: 1.8;
			}

			.back-link {
				border-top: 1px solid #333;
			}
		</style>
	</head>
	<body>
		<div class="container">
			<article>
				<header class="post-header">
					<h1>{post.title}</h1>
					<div class="post-meta">
						<span>{post.date}</span>
						<span>•</span>
						<span>{post.author}</span>
					</div>
				</header>

				<div class="post-content">
					<p>
						This is the first post on the new blog setup. Just testing out the
						structure and styling to make sure everything flows right.
					</p>

					<h2>Why a Blog?</h2>

					<p>
						Figured it was time to document some of the projects, experiments,
						and random thoughts that come up while building stuff. Nothing too
						formal—just notes and observations.
					</p>

					<h3>What to Expect</h3>

					<ul>
						<li>Web dev techniques and tricks I pick up along the way</li>
						<li>Thoughts on design, UX, and user experience</li>
						<li>Project breakdowns and case studies</li>
						<li>Occasional deep dives on interesting problems</li>
					</ul>

					<p>
						No set schedule. Posts happen when there's something worth sharing.
					</p>

					<h2>The Tech Stack</h2>

					<p>
						This blog runs on <a href="https://astro.build/" target="_blank"
							>Astro</a
						>, keeping it simple and fast. Static generation, minimal
						JavaScript, maximum performance.
					</p>

					<blockquote>
						"The best code is the code you don't have to write."
					</blockquote>

					<p>
						Each post is just an <code>.astro</code> file. No database, no complex
						CMS—just files and git commits. Clean, version-controlled, and easy to
						maintain.
					</p>

					<h2>Stay Tuned</h2>

					<p>
						More posts coming soon. If you want to get in touch about projects
						or just want to chat about web dev, hit me up at <a
							href="mailto:web@xaaane.com">web@xaaane.com</a
						>.
					</p>

					<p style="margin-top: 2rem; color: #666;">— Xane</p>
				</div>
			</article>

			<div class="back-link">
				<a href="/blog">← Back to Blog</a>
			</div>
		</div>
	</body>
</html>
